text: It's important to recognize how @KamalaHarris' plan for increased teacher pay directly helps kids. Teaching conditions are learning conditions. By investing in the people who spend every day with students, we're investing in students.
author: asherhuey

text: You've seen the walkouts across the country. Underpaying teachers and not investing in public ed has become a national crisis. This plan from @KamalaHarris addresses it head on and it's what America needs. https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-kamala-harris-teacher-pay-20190323-story.html …
author: asherhuey

text: It's basic labor economics. If you don't pay teachers enough, compared to other professions with similar degree requirements, then you won't recruit and retain enough high-quality teachers. https://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-pol-kamala-harris-teacher-pay-20190323-story.html …
author: asherhuey

text: This is a great move from @KamalaHarris. If we actually believe that education is important, then we have to invest in paying teachers.
